# Alias .qkt files to SQL for github.com syntax highlighting.
# Linguist won't accept qkt as a first-class language until the popularity
# bar is met (200+ public repos). SQL is the closest shape — covers comments,
# strings, numbers, and a portion of keywords (CASE/WHEN/AND/OR/NOT/IN/BETWEEN/AS).
# Local editors use the real grammar at editor/textmate/qkt.tmLanguage.json.
*.qkt linguist-language=SQL
